<h2>Case Study #1: How G2 Grew from 50,000 to 1 Million Sessions Per Year</h2>
<p>G2, the B2B software review platform, grew organic blog traffic from 50,000 to 1 million sessions per year. That is a 1,900% increase in 12 months.</p>
<p>The strategy was not complicated. It was disciplined. G2 focused on three things: complete keyword research, competitor content gaps, and topic clusters.</p>
<h3>The Strategy Breakdown</h3>
<p><strong>Keyword research at scale.</strong> G2 identified thousands of software comparison and review keywords. They did not just target "best CRM software." They targeted "best CRM software for small business," "best CRM software for real estate," and "best free CRM software." Each long-tail variation became a dedicated post.</p>
<p><strong>Competitor gap analysis.</strong> G2 analyzed what their competitors ranked for that they did not. They used tools like Ahrefs and Semrush to find high-traffic keywords with weak content. Then they created better, more complete pages.</p>
<p><strong>Topic clusters.</strong> G2 organized content into clusters. A pillar page on "CRM software" linked to 20+ cluster posts on specific CRM tools, use cases, and comparisons. This internal linking structure told Google that G2 owned the CRM topic.</p>
