<p>Every post you write should aim to be the best resource on that topic. Not the longest. The best. The most helpful. The most accurate. The most current.</p>
<h3>Step 4: Optimize for Featured Snippets and AI Overviews</h3>
<p>Featured snippets capture 8.6% of clicks. AI Overviews appear on 47% of search queries. Optimizing for both is no longer optional.</p>
<p><strong>For featured snippets:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Answer the target question in 40-60 words within the first paragraph</li>
<li>Use numbered lists for "how to" queries</li>
<li>Use bullet lists for "best" and "types of" queries</li>
<li>Use comparison tables for "vs" queries</li>
<li>Include the target keyword in the first 100 words</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For AI Overviews:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Structure content with clear H2 and H3 headings</li>
<li>Include FAQ sections with direct answers</li>
<li>Use schema markup (FAQPage, HowTo, Article)</li>
<li>Cite authoritative sources by name</li>
<li>Update content within the last 30 days (AI Overviews favor fresh content)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Step 5: Build Strategic Internal Links</h3>
<p>Internal linking is the most underused SEO tactic. It distributes link equity, establishes topical authority, and keeps readers on your site longer.</p>
<p>Rules for internal linking:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Link from new posts to 3-5 related existing posts</li>
<li>[ ] Link from old posts to new posts within 48 hours of publishing</li>
<li>[ ] Use descriptive anchor text (not "click here")</li>
<li>[ ] Create content clusters with pillar pages linking to cluster posts</li>
<li>[ ] Add a "related posts" section at the end of every article</li>
<li>[ ] Link to your most important pages from your navigation and footer</li>
</ul>
<p>A strong internal linking structure can increase organic traffic by 10-40% without creating new content.</p>
<h3>Step 6: Refresh Old Content Quarterly</h3>
<p>Content decay is real. A post that ranked #1 six months ago might be on page 2 today. Competitors publish better content. Information becomes outdated. Links break.</p>
<p>The refresh process:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Update statistics with current data</li>
<li>[ ] Add new sections to cover emerging subtopics</li>
<li>[ ] Improve readability and formatting</li>
<li>[ ] Add new internal links to recent posts</li>
<li>[ ] Update the publish date in the frontmatter</li>
<li>[ ] Check and fix broken external links</li>
<li>[ ] Add new images or refresh existing ones</li>
<li>[ ] Expand thin sections with more detail</li>
</ul>
<p>According to <a href="https://www.hubspot.com/marketing-statistics">HubSpot</a>, updating old blog posts can increase organic traffic by 106% on average.</p>
