<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<p><strong>How long does blog SEO take to show results?</strong></p>
<p>Most blogs see initial ranking movement within 30-60 days. Significant traffic growth typically takes 4-6 months. The case studies in this guide show results timelines of 6-12 months. SEO compounds over time. Month 6 traffic is usually 3-5x month 3 traffic.</p>
<p><strong>What is the best publishing frequency for blog SEO?</strong></p>
<p>HubSpot data shows companies publishing 16+ posts per month get 4.5x more leads than those publishing 4 or fewer. For most businesses, 4-8 quality posts per month is the sweet spot. Consistency matters more than volume.</p>
<p><strong>How important are backlinks for blog SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Backlinks remain one of the top 3 ranking factors. However, quality matters more than quantity. One link from a high-authority site in your niche is worth more than 50 low-quality links. Focus on creating link-worthy content first.</p>
<p><strong>Should I update old blog posts or write new ones?</strong></p>
<p>Both. Update old posts quarterly to protect existing rankings. Write new posts to expand your keyword coverage. A good ratio is 1 new post for every 2-3 updated posts. Updated posts often drive faster traffic gains than new posts.</p>
<p><strong>How do I know if my blog content is high quality?</strong></p>
